      "content": "i get that, but i've been reading online that garlic extract actually has very strong anticoagulant properties, almost like a natural warfarin. if i started taking a really high dose of it every day, couldn't that do the job for me so i don't have to deal with the side effects of the pills and the tests anymore? like what kind of amount would i need to be looking at to actually see a change in my clotting?",
